<paragraph id="8BA2C620FFF4060FF8F4FAF77AC0FAE5" blockId="17.[138,233,1284,1308]" box="[138,233,1284,1308]" pageId="17" pageNumber="3385">
<emphasis id="B9691A32FFF4060FF8F4FAF77AC0FAE5" box="[138,233,1284,1308]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="3385">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA2C620FFF4060FF8F4FAC67E8BF968" blockId="17.[138,1186,1333,1681]" pageId="17" pageNumber="3385">
Thus far, few illustrations have been published. Only K. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8CBBD1FFF4060FFB20FAC679DEFAB4" author="Viets K" box="[862,1015,1333,1357]" pageId="17" pageNumber="3385" pagination="329 - 350" refId="ref11816" refString="Viets K. 1914. Hydracarinen aus dem Kaplande. Gesammelt von der Deutschen Sudpolar-Expedition. Zoologische Jahrbucher, Abteilung fur Systematik, Geographie und Biologie der Tiere 37: 329 - 350." type="journal article" year="1914">Viets (1914)</bibRefCitation>
published an illustration of the female palp in his original description. Later on, K. O. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8CBBD1FFF4060FFC72FAA57E88FA97" author="Viets KO" box="[1036,1185,1366,1390]" pageId="17" pageNumber="3385" pagination="467 - 485" refId="ref11940" refString="Viets KO. 1963. Hygrobatidae (Acari, Hydrachnellae) aus Sudafrika. Archiv fur Hydrobiologie 59: 467 - 485." type="journal article" year="1963">Viets (1963)</bibRefCitation>
published more records of the species with more measurements, however, without illustrations. Therefore, more illustrations are provided here, as well as more measurements, especially of the legs (see Table II). For differences with 
<taxonomicName id="4C1DBDA3FFF4060FFA36FA44797FFA36" authorityName="Smit" authorityYear="2005" box="[584,854,1463,1487]" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Hygrobates" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="3385" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inflatipes" subGenus="Inflatibates">
<emphasis id="B9691A32FFF4060FFA36FA44797FFA36" box="[584,854,1463,1487]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="3385">H. (Inflatibates) inflatipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
see under the latter. K. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8CBBD1FFF4060FFC14FA447AFFFA16" author="Viets K" pageId="17" pageNumber="3385" pagination="1 - 31" refId="ref11884" refString="Viets K. 1956. Wassermilben aus Sudafrika. Systematische, faunistische und okologische Untersuchungen. Zoologische Jahrbucher, Abteilung fur Systematik, Geographie und Biologie der Tiere 84: 1 - 31." type="journal article" year="1956">Viets (1956)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="4C1DBDA3FFF4060FF938FA2B780AFA16" box="[326,547,1495,1519]" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Hygrobates" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="3385" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="sigthori" subSpecies="rubicundus">
<emphasis id="B9691A32FFF4060FF938FA2B780AFA16" box="[326,547,1495,1519]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="3385">H. sigthori rubicundus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on a different genital skeleton of the male. In the slide with the 
<typeStatus id="54A67882FFF4060FF89AFA0B7B6AF9E9" box="[228,323,1528,1552]" pageId="17" pageNumber="3385">holotype</typeStatus>
male (7779, SMF), 
<specimenCount id="9D1B0DA9FFF4060FFA65FA0B78AEF9E9" box="[539,647,1528,1552]" pageId="17" pageNumber="3385" type="male">two males</specimenCount>
are present. The genital skeleton of the male which probably represents the 
<typeStatus id="54A67882FFF4060FF9EAF9EB7BDAF9C9" box="[404,499,1560,1584]" pageId="17" pageNumber="3385">holotype</typeStatus>
is lying free in the slide. This genital skeleton is similar to the nominate form. The other male has a genital skeleton as described by K. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8CBBD1FFF4060FFBBFF9CB7E67F9A9" author="Viets K" box="[961,1102,1592,1616]" pageId="17" pageNumber="3385" pagination="1 - 31" refId="ref11884" refString="Viets K. 1956. Wassermilben aus Sudafrika. Systematische, faunistische und okologische Untersuchungen. Zoologische Jahrbucher, Abteilung fur Systematik, Geographie und Biologie der Tiere 84: 1 - 31." type="journal article" year="1956">Viets (1956)</bibRefCitation>
, with a vesicular part between the arms of the genital skeleton.The females are in my opinion similar.More material is needed before the separate taxonomical status of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1DBDA3FFF4060FFB7EF98979F4F968" box="[768,989,1657,1681]" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Hygrobates" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="17" pageNumber="3385" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="sigthori" subSpecies="rubicundus">
<emphasis id="B9691A32FFF4060FFB7EF98979F4F968" box="[768,989,1657,1681]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="3385">H. sigthori rubicundus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be confirmed.
</paragraph>
